universe u v

variable {ő© : Type u} [MeasurableSpace ő©]
variable {E : Type v} [MeasurableSpace E]

/-- BSDEJ data: terminal condition `g`, generator `f`.

**Scope note (red-team M10, 2026-05-22)**: `Y` is scalar-valued
(`g : (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ` and the `f` driver returns `‚ĄĚ`). This matches the
literature references actually used by this library:

* Tang & Li 1994 SIAM J. Control Optim. 32(5), Theorem 3.1 ‚ÄĒ scalar `Y`.
* Andersson-Gnoatto-Patacca-Picarelli 2025 arXiv:2211.04349 Theorem 2.4 ‚ÄĒ
  scalar `Y`.
* Bouchard & Elie 2008 SPA 118(1) Theorem 2.1 ‚ÄĒ scalar `Y`.

Vector-`Y` BSDEJs (reflected, quadratic-growth, FBSDEJ couples) require a
different existence-uniqueness apparatus and are **outside the current
scope**. A vector-`Y` generalization would parameterize this structure by
an additional `m : ‚Ąē` (the `Y`-dimension) and change `g : (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí
(Fin m ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)`, `f : ‚Ä¶ ‚Üí (Fin m ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)`. Tracked as future work; not a defect
in the present scalar-`Y` chain.

**Measurability invariants (red-team 2nd audit P12 F4, 2026-05-23)**:
`BSDEJData` now carries `f_measurable` and `g_measurable` as structural
fields, so that downstream `IsBSDEJSolution` cannot be evaluated on
pathological non-measurable drivers (where the Bochner integral
`integral_undef`-defaults to 0, making the BSDEJ equation `Y_t = g + 0`
trivially solvable). Both fields use the joint measurability appropriate
for the integrand role:
- `g : (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ` is jointly Borel-measurable in `x`.
- `f : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí (E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ` is jointly
  measurable in its 5 arguments (modulo the (E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) slot which uses the
  product ŌÉ-algebra on E-indexed reals ‚ÄĒ appropriate for the
  `ő®_t = ‚ąę U_t(z) őĹ(dz)` channel). -/
structure BSDEJData (n d : ‚Ąē) (E : Type v) where
  /-- Generator `f(t, x, y, z, u)`. -/
  f : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí (E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ
  /-- Terminal condition `g(x)`. -/
  g : (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ
  /-- `g` is Borel-measurable. -/
  g_measurable : Measurable g
  /-- `f` is jointly measurable in `(t, x, y, z, u)`. The 5-arg product
  ŌÉ-algebra is the canonical one on
  `‚ĄĚ √ó (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) √ó (E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)`. -/
  f_measurable : Measurable (fun (p : ‚ĄĚ √ó (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) √ó (E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)) =>
    f p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2.1 p.2.2.2.1 p.2.2.2.2)

/-- Predicate: `(Y, Z, U)` solves the BSDEJ with data `bsdej`, driven by
`(W, N)` and the forward process `X`, on the time horizon `[0, T]`.

See module docstring for the 2026-05-11 strengthening that replaced a
vacuous per-`(t, ŌČ)` existential with an outer existential of two
process martingales `M_W, M_N` constrained to `Z, U` via L¬≤-isometry +
direct compensated-Poisson-integral pin. -/
def IsBSDEJSolution
    {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
    {n d : ‚Ąē}
    (W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ)
    (bsdej : BSDEJData n d E)
    (X : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ))
    (Y : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (Z : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin d ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ))
    (U : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí E ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)
    (T : ‚ĄĚ) : Prop :=
  Measurable (Function.uncurry Y)
    ‚ąß (‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, (‚®Ü t ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T, (‚ÄĖY t ŌČ‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2) ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
    ‚ąß (‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T,
        ‚ąĎ i, (‚ÄĖZ s ŌČ i‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
    ‚ąß (‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ e,
        (‚ÄĖU s ŌČ e‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāőĹ ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§)
    -- 2026-05-23 strengthening (P4 H c√†dl√†g fix): Tang-Li / Pardoux-RńÉŇücanu
    -- solution space `S¬≤` requires Y to be c√†dl√†g-adapted. The previous
    -- joint-measurability-only requirement was strictly weaker (e.g., the
    -- supremum `‚®Ü t ‚ąą [0,T] ‚ÄĖY_t‚ÄĖ¬≤` above is ill-typed as a measurable
    -- function of ŌČ without c√†dl√†g paths). Adding `Y_cadlag` makes the
    -- supremum honestly measurable and matches the literature S¬≤ space.
    ‚ąß (‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
        Filter.Tendsto (fun s => Y s ŌČ) (nhdsWithin t (Set.Ioi t)) (nhds (Y t ŌČ))
          ‚ąß ‚ąÉ L : ‚ĄĚ,
              Filter.Tendsto (fun s => Y s ŌČ) (nhdsWithin t (Set.Iio t)) (nhds L))
    -- 2026-05-21 strengthening 1: adaptedness layer (rules out
    -- Y = W‚āĀ_T ‚ąí W‚āĀ_t counterexample).
    -- 2026-05-22 strengthening 2 (H2 fix): M_W is now PINNED to the
    -- canonical multidim Brownian It√ī integral of Z (not just L¬≤-isometric).
    -- This requires the per-component Z hypotheses (joint measurability,
    -- progressive measurability w.r.t. W's component natural filtrations,
    -- per-component L¬≤ bound) to be bundled inside the existential.
    -- 2026-05-23 strengthening 3 (M11-CRIT fix per red-team 2nd-audit P12):
    -- `Filt` was previously existential with the constraint
    -- `naturalFiltration ‚Č§ Filt`, but that constraint is satisfied vacuously
    -- by `Filt = ‚ä§` (the maximal filtration), defeating the stated
    -- "rule out trivial constant filtrations" purpose. Now pinned EXACTLY
    -- to the **right-continuous augmentation** of the join of natural
    -- filtrations via `Filt = joint_natural.rightCont` inside the existential,
    -- where `joint_natural := (‚®Ü i, naturalFiltration (W.W i)) ‚äĒ naturalFiltration N`
    -- (literature `ŌÉ(W, N) = ‚®ÜŠĶĘ ŌÉ(W_i) ‚ą® ŌÉ(N)`).
    -- P7 F4 closure (red-team 2nd audit, 2026-05-23): Tang-Li 1994 /
    -- Pardoux-RńÉŇücanu solution space uses the right-continuous augmented
    -- filtration (needed for Doob's L¬≤-maximal, optional stopping, c√†dl√†g
    -- modification). Previous version used the RAW natural filtration ‚ÄĒ
    -- strictly weaker than literature. `.rightCont` is the Mathlib operator
    -- for right-continuization; the P-null-set augmentation step is a
    -- separate strengthening (deferred ‚ÄĒ Mathlib lacks a clean primitive).
    ‚ąß (‚ąÉ Filt : MeasureTheory.Filtration ‚ĄĚ ‚ÄĻMeasurableSpace ő©‚Äļ,
        Filt = ((‚®Ü i : Fin d,
                  LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i))
                  ‚äĒ LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).rightCont ‚ąß
        -- P4 F1 fix (red-team 2nd audit, 2026-05-23): Tang-Li 1994 /
        -- Pardoux-RńÉŇücanu 2014 / Bichteler use the solution space
        -- `S¬≤ √ó H¬≤ √ó H¬≤_N` where H¬≤ is the L¬≤ space of PROGRESSIVELY
        -- MEASURABLE (= ProgMeasurable Filt, equivalent to predictable
        -- under the usual hypotheses on Filt) processes. The previous
        -- `Adapted Filt Z` / `Adapted Filt (fun s ŌČ => U s ŌČ e)` were
        -- per-t measurable only and did NOT imply joint measurability
        -- on the progressive ŌÉ-algebra. Strengthened to ProgMeasurable
        -- for Z and U_e (Y stays Adapted since it's the S¬≤-c√†dl√†g leg).
        MeasureTheory.Adapted Filt Y ‚ąß
        MeasureTheory.IsStronglyProgressive Filt Z ‚ąß
        (‚ąÄ e : E, MeasureTheory.IsStronglyProgressive Filt (fun s ŌČ => U s ŌČ e)) ‚ąß
        ‚ąÉ M_W M_N : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ,
          Measurable (Function.uncurry M_W) ‚ąß
          Measurable (Function.uncurry M_N) ‚ąß
          MeasureTheory.Adapted Filt M_W ‚ąß
          MeasureTheory.Adapted Filt M_N ‚ąß
          -- M_W is PINNED to the canonical multidim Brownian It√ī integral of Z.
          -- Hypotheses on Z (per-component measurability / progressive measurability
          -- / L¬≤-bound) are bundled inside this existential so that
          -- `MultidimBrownianMotion.stochasticIntegral W Z ... T'` is well-typed.
          (‚ąÉ (h_Z_meas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d,
                Measurable (Function.uncurry (fun ŌČ s => Z s ŌČ i)))
             (h_Z_progMeas : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
                @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ) ‚ĄĚ _
                  (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© ‚ĄĚ
                    ((LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Martingale.naturalFiltration (W.W i)).seq t)
                    inferInstance)
                  (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ => Z p.2 p.1 i))
             (h_Z_sq : ‚ąÄ i : Fin d, ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
                ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T',
                  (‚ÄĖZ s ŌČ i‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2 ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§),
            ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP,
              M_W T' ŌČ =
                LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion.stochasticIntegral
                  W Z h_Z_meas h_Z_progMeas h_Z_sq T' ŌČ) ‚ąß
          -- M_N is pinned to the canonical compensated-Poisson L¬≤ integral of U.
          -- H6 fix (red-team 2nd audit, 2026-05-23): U-side hypotheses bundled
          -- here (mirror of how M_W bundles h_Z hypotheses). Closes the prior
          -- "hollow M_N pin" issue (Persona 7 F1+F2) where per-e adaptedness
          -- of U was insufficient.
          (‚ąÉ (h_U_meas : Measurable
                (fun (p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) =>
                  (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
             (h_U_progMeas : ‚ąÄ t : ‚ĄĚ,
                @MeasureTheory.StronglyMeasurable (ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E) ‚ĄĚ _
                  (@Prod.instMeasurableSpace ő© (‚ĄĚ √ó E)
                    ((LevyStochCalc.Poisson.naturalFiltration N).seq t)
                    inferInstance)
                  (fun p : ő© √ó ‚ĄĚ √ó E => (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2))
             (h_U_sq : ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < T' ‚Üí
                ‚ąę‚ĀĽ ŌČ, ‚ąę‚ĀĽ s in Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T', ‚ąę‚ĀĽ e,
                  (‚ÄĖ(fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) ŌČ s e‚ÄĖ‚āä : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) ^ 2
                    ‚ąāőĹ ‚ąāvolume ‚ąāP < ‚ä§),
            ‚ąÄ T' : ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP,
              M_N T' ŌČ =
                LevyStochCalc.Poisson.Compensated.stochasticIntegral N
                  (fun ŌČ' s e => U s ŌČ' e) h_U_meas h_U_progMeas h_U_sq T' ŌČ) ‚ąß
          -- M_W and M_N are martingales w.r.t. the same Filt:
          MeasureTheory.Martingale M_W Filt P ‚ąß
          MeasureTheory.Martingale M_N Filt P ‚ąß
          -- BSDEJ equation at every t, with the same (M_W, M_N):
          (‚ąÄ t ‚ąą Set.Icc (0 : ‚ĄĚ) T, ‚ąÄŠĶź ŌČ ‚ąāP,
            Y t ŌČ = bsdej.g (X T ŌČ)
              + ‚ąę s in Set.Icc t T,
                  bsdej.f s (X s ŌČ) (Y s ŌČ) (Z s ŌČ) (U s ŌČ)
              - (M_W T ŌČ - M_W t ŌČ) - (M_N T ŌČ - M_N t ŌČ)))

/-! ## Structural regression tests for `IsBSDEJSolution`

These extractor theorems are the structural canary for the `IsBSDEJSolution`
predicate's literature-strength conjuncts. If anyone weakens the predicate
(e.g., relaxes the `Filt` pin to a `‚Č§ Filt` constraint, demotes
`IsStronglyProgressive` back to `Adapted`, removes the canonical-integral
pins on `M_W`/`M_N`, or drops the c√†dl√†g paths on `Y`), these theorems will
fail to elaborate and the build will break ‚ÄĒ exactly the kind of soundness
regression that the P12 F1 red-team counterexample
(`Y‚āĀ = 0` vs `Y‚āā = W_T ‚ąí W_t` both satisfying a weakened predicate) was
designed to catch.

The tests are deliberately load-bearing: each one extracts a single
strengthening as a public extractor, so it can be both (a) consumed by
downstream callers needing the strengthening, and (b) used as a build-time
regression check on the predicate's surface API. -/

namespace IsBSDEJSolution

variable {P : Measure ő©} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
variable {őĹ : Measure E} [SigmaFinite őĹ]
variable {n d : ‚Ąē}
variable {W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d}
variable {N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P őĹ}
variable {bsdej : BSDEJData n d E}
variable {X : ‚ĄĚ ‚Üí ő© ‚Üí (Fin n ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)}
